children.subject: 168 is a nice class if you're looking for a more relaxing semester. There's no real homework, just the material and a few projects. It's also interesting learning about the design choices behind the internet and its infrastructure. 188 covers a broad range of topics in trying to get computers to behave intelligently and isn't limited to just ML, but it isn't essential. Not sure about 169L.

history.content:
rising third-year student, will be my last year.  Dual CS/DS major. I'm planning out my schedule for next year and my last semester.  CS 189 is my last required class (DS MLDM requirement).  Just trying to solicit some ideas for my 2 other classes.  I'd like it to be a bit more relaxing semester since I might be recruiting - I like many others got screwed out of my internship earlier this month so I'm not sure what I'm going to do with myself.  I've taken 4 techs for 3 straight semesters (including Fall 2020) and my GPA has suffered a bit for it.   Uppers I have taken/will take:  Data 100, Data 144, CS 161, 162, 164, 170, 176, 186, STAT 140, BIOENG 145, COGSCI 131.

Ordinarily I might have taken 188 and perhaps INFO 159, but I dunno about ML and Cognition any more.  I feel like too many people are into it and I prefer not to be a lemming.  I wished there were more sports analytics like the Data 88 connector, or something similar.  I really do like the quantitative side of Computational Biology, so far.

Am I going to regret not taking 188? Is taking CS 169L worth it with 189?  168 any good?  Any other ideas?  I doubt if I'd qualify for grad school (maybe 2 years ago but not now).
history.subject: Spring 2021 - what to take besides 189
